Commentary Text: Shami to Conway, out Caught by Saha!! Gone! Conway falls early! Pitched up from round the wicket, it's angled in on off and Conway is looking for an on-drive with his bat-face towards mid-on. But the ball straightens slightly, takes the edge and it's regulation for Saha. Also the length wasn't that full either. Conway was reaching in front of the body, having already shimmied down. Conway c Saha b Shami 5(9)

Commentary Text: Matheesha Pathirana to Shubman Gill, out Lbw!! It's Wankhede, it's a slingy action from right arm pacer but it's not Lasith Malinga. It's his disciple, Matheesha Pathirana. A first ball wicket on IPL debut for the Under19 star. Wow! Bowled a pacy full delivery that completely foxed Gill. Totally late on the shot and the ball escaped past the bat to hit him low on the pad. Impact in line with leg stump and crashing into leg stump. Review wasted by GT. Malinga sure is in his drills in the Royals camp a few metres away from this ground, but when he sees the replay he will have a big smile on his face. Joy for the youngster as he sees the whole DRS process on the big screen. Shubman Gill lbw b Matheesha Pathirana 18(17) [4s-3]
